This paper deals with the study of influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to optimize the spread of information, which is relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of access gaps in information dissemination, which is related to the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper proposes a maximin social welfare function as an objective function, which is relevant to the sub-category of social choice (cs.SI).
